---
title: Modal
---
p.-text Modals are windows used for displaying prompts and subtasks without losing context of the parent application.

.m-alert.-bubble.-info
  i.a-icon.-sm--2.icon-circle-info.-text--info
  | This component requires Javascript

h3 Examples
p.-text
  | Modals are composed of several parts. To render a modal, include a modal backdrop, modal header, modal body,
  | and modal footer (optional).
  | By default modals are positioned on top of the page.

h4 Base
.example.-mb--3
  .m-backdrop.-p--6.-position--relative.-z--0(style="border-top-left-radius:3px;border-top-right-radius:3px;")
    .m-backdrop__wrapper
      .a-modal
        .a-modal__header
          h3.a-modal__title Modal Title
          button(class='a-btn -icon -close')
            .a-btn__content
              i.a-icon.icon-x
        .a-modal__content
          p.-text.-m--0 Modal content
        .a-modal__footer
          button.a-btn Cancel
          button.a-btn.-primary.-ml--2 Save
  :code(lang="html")
    <div class="m-backdrop">
      <div class="m-backdrop__wrapper">
        <div class="a-modal">
          <div class="a-modal__header">
            <h3 class="a-modal__title">Modal Title</h3>
            <button class="a-btn -icon -close">
              <div class="a-btn__content">
                <i class="a-icon icon-x"></i>
              </div>
            </button>
          </div>
          <div class="a-modal__content">
            <p class="-text -m--0">Modal content</p>
          </div>
          <div class="a-modal__footer">
            <button class="a-btn">Cancel</button>
            <button class="a-btn -primary -ml--2">Save</button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

